719288f-b.title: Manhattan: Delancey Street - Suffolk Street
719288f-b.text:
(1)
154 Delancey Street, north side, between Suffolk and Clinton
Streets. The view shows the lower stories only.
September 20, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
weo ~ 1130
(2)
The same view, showing No. 164 Delancey Street, at the N.W.
corner of Clinton Street. The view shows the lower stories only.
September 20, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
The building shown in No. 2 bearing Nos. 156-164 Delancey Street
and No. 1072 Clinton Street is to be replaced by a one story business
structure accordink to the New York Times of May 3, 1938.
